<h1 id="privacyTitle">Privacy Policy</h1>

<div>
	<h2>Introduction</h2>

	<p>This Privacy Policy outlines our commitment to protecting the privacy and security of your personal health information (PHI) in compliance with the Health Insurance Portability and Accountability Act (HIPAA) and 10DLC registration requirements.</p>
</div>

<div>
	<h2>Notice of Privacy Practices</h2>

	<p>We are required by law to maintain the privacy of your PHI and provide you with this Notice of Privacy Practices. This document describes how we use and disclose your PHI, your rights regarding your PHI, and our legal duties to protect your PHI.</p>
</div>

<div>
	<h2>Use and Disclosure of PHI</h2>

	<p>We may use and disclose your PHI for the following purposes:</p>

	<ol>
		<li><strong>Treatment: </strong> We may use your PHI to provide you with medical care, including medication management for esketamine, ketamine, and TMS.</li>
		<li><strong>Payment: </strong> We may use your PHI to bill and receive payment for the serviceswe provide.</li>
		<li><strong>Health Care Operations: </strong> We may use your PHI to manage and improve the quality of care we provide.</li>
		<li><strong>Appointment Reminders:</strong> We may use your PHI to remind you of upcoming appointments.</li>
		<li><strong>Treatment Alternatives and Health-Related Benefits and Services:</strong> We may use your PHI to inform you about treatment alternatives or health-related benefits and services that may be of interest to you.</li>
		<li><strong>Individuals Involved in Your Care:</strong> We may share your PHI with individuals involved in your care, such as family members or close friends, when appropriate.</li>
		<li><strong>Research:</strong> We may use your PHI for research purposes under certain circumstances.</li>
	</ol>
</div>

<div>
	<h2>Your Rights</h2>

	<p>Your have the rights to:</p>
	<ol>
		<li><strong>Request Access to Your PHI:</strong> You can request a copy of your PHI.</li>
		<li><strong>Request Ammendments:</strong> You can request corrections to your PHI if you believe it is inaccurate or incomplete.</li>
		<li><strong>Request Restrictions:</strong> You can request restrictions on how we use and disclose your PHI.</li>
		<li><strong>Request Confidential Communications:</strong> You can request that we communicate with you in a certain way or at a certain location.</li>
		<li><strong>receive a Notice of Privacy Practices:</strong> You have the right to receive a copy of this Privacy Policy.</li>
		<li><strong>File a Complaint:</strong> You have the right to file a complaint with us or the U.S. Department of Health and Human Services if you believe your privacy rights have been violated.</li>
	</ol>
</div>

<div>
	<h2>10DLC Registration Compliance</h2>

	<p>To comply with 10DLC registration requirements, we have registered our 10-digit long code phone number with The Campaign Registry (TCR). This ensures that our text messages are not marked as spam and are delivered to your phone. We follow all industry best practices, including obtaining prior express written consent before texting any consumer and providing clear opt-out instructions in the first text of any campaign2.</p>
</div>

<div>
	<h2>Security Measures</h2>

	<p>We take the security of your PHI seriously and have implemented various measures to protect it, including:</p>
	<ol>
		<li><strong>Access Controls:</strong> Only authorized personnel have access to your PHI.</li>
		<li><strong>Encryption:</strong> We use encryption to protect your PHI when it is stored or transmitted electronically.</li>
		<li><strong>Training:</strong> Our staff receives regular training on privacy and security practices.</li>
	</ol>
</div>

